label.value: coronavirus host role

definition.value: A host role that is played by an organism and realized by providing nourishment, shelter or a means of reproduction to a coronavirus.

label.value: human coronavirus host role

definition.value: A virus host role that is played by an organism and realized by providing nourishment, shelter or a means of reproduction to a coronavirus that can infect human. Note that in addition to human, many other organisms (e.g., deer and dog) can also serve as the human coronavirus host role.

label.value: natural human coronavirus host role

definition.value: A virus host role that is played by an organism and realized by providing nourishment, shelter or a means of reproduction to a human coronavirus at a natural environmental condition.
